I always say september is my favorite month of the year. maybe it’s because the weather is finally perfect in the city and even though the sun is setting earlier by the day, it feels like summer is just beginning. maybe it’s because I take my yearly vacation every september - just sand and sweaty walks and burritos and tan lines and strong margs and orange skies. maybe it’s because when I inevitably come home again, a little more golden and soft, I feel a renewed sense of gratitude - for my friends, my life, and the privilege of playtime. it’s like in september the sand smoothes away all the roughness from the past eight months and I’m able to gracefully slip into fall, raw and shiny 💛

perfect bites I can’t stop thinking about, sd edition:

some places just feel like home the second you step foot in them and new orleans was like that for me. maybe it’s the humidity or the brick sidewalks or the way the trees line the streets and make shady archways. or maybe it’s the way people here take things day by day, enjoying things when they can - or the way despite everything they’ve been through and continue to go through, they find joy and sit on the front porch and wish you a good morning. maybe it’s all of it or none of it - maybe I was always meant to be in new orleans a week before going back to argentina, with familiar breadcrumbs everywhere I looked ❤️

october was heatwaves, fans, fall sweaters, pool days, cozy hot tubs, dancing at music festivals, victoria monet, inji, kim petras, zhu, cabin getaways, seattle, new orleans, swimming in caves, grilling, celebrating love, last minute costumes, new traditions 💘

POV: you call out a brand for stealing your content and they double down even though Meta ads are public 🫣🫣

never forget your rights as a creator! as a full time freelance influencer marketing specialist and content creator, I will *always* speak up about fair compensation for creators and ethical brand practices. last week was a doozy but I so so so appreciate my community’s help, support, and advocacy. the creator community is more powerful together ❤️

for those asking for updates, I’ve decided work with @juliansarafian @forcreatorsbycreatorspc who represents creators in this scenario. thank you so much @_itsmaggiez for the recommendation! 

lmk if you want a story time or more updates we go - appreciate you always! 🙏

how to use meta ads library 🫡

as a creator: helpful for verifying if brands are illegally using your content - whether that means stealing your content completely or extending the usage period beyond what was agreed upon in a contract (ex. the contract says 30 days usage and they used it for 31+) 

as a brand: competitor research, ad inspiration and positioning, + keeping everyone honest!! 

hope this is helpful! ❤️
how has this month flown by so quickly! second to last day left in argentina before heading back to sf 🥲🩵

foods I demand you eat if you ever find yourself in argentina or we’re in a fight 😤👇

- breakfast or merienda: medialuna de manteca (con jamón y queso for more savory vibes), tostado con pan de miga de jamón y queso, fresh squeezed orange juice, lots of coffee
- lunch: milanesa, empanadas (carne or cebolla y queso are my favs!), picadas aka charcuterie plates 
- parrilla: provoleta (literally a hunk of grilled, crispy, gooey, salty cheese), chorizo, ojo de bife, matambrito de cerdo
- sweets: alfajores, panqueque de dulce de leche, lots of ice cream (dulce de leche of course + banana split aka my fav) 

🥐🧉🩵🥰

our favorite new restaurant of 2023 🌟 Matt and I were absolutely blown away by our meal at @eatatpippal ! 

every single dish we ordered was delicious, thoughtful, and beautifully presented. the space was perfect for a date night or special meal, and the team was super helpful and knowledgeable. cocktails are also an *absolute* must - all inspired by landmarks in india. everything we ordered:

- pan seared chicken momo with chili chutney 
- burrah kebab: lamb chops with mint chili chutney 
- goan chorizo pulao with fried onion, crispy bacon, and garlic raita 
- kerala dungeness crab masala with lemongrass and coconut 
- chili garlic naan 

can’t wait to go back in 2024! a must try ❤️
